        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 1:10PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 110 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 18
miles north of Walhalla, or 4 miles south of Cashiers, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Cashiers, Lake Toxaway, Graveyard Fields, Looking Glass, Mount
Pisgah, Black Balsam Area, Gorges State Park, Highlands, B.R.
Parkway-Black Balsam To Mount Pisgah, and B.R. Parkway-Balsam Gap To
Black Balsam Area.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
